 you may have heard of the vs raid I led a little over a week ago that wiped twice. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Well, I'm planning to try him again, with better results this time, but it seems my current tactic is flawed.<br>
<br>
Clear to the staging room. Either use a ranger to calm pull the excess mobs, or have a necro FD/eye pull. (Either works. Ghallion did a tight job using the FD/Eye method.)<br>
<br>
Key classes included 2 chanters (neither epic enabled) 3 clerics (1 epic) and a 60 mage (for mala) We definatly had enough tanks.<br>
<br>
The problem was, even with 2 chanters chain runeing the MA, and VS being slowed, he would still manage to get a few lifetaps through. With the 3 clerics doing cheal rotation, we got him down to about 35%, but the chanters went oom from chain runes, and the clerics soon after that. By that time he had healed himself back up to over 50% from the lifetaps.<br>
<br>
The necro (only had 1) instead of twitching the clerics (which isnt very efficient with just 1 necro) he had a charmed undead wailing on VS, which seemed to help quite a bit. <br>
<br>
Aside from the two wipeouts, the fooking memory leaks made it extremely hard to respond too all the incoming tells, of questions, and crap I was getting since I was leading the raid. After that experience, I begin to wonder why I even chose to organize that raid. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Next time I'm definatly going to assign more people to help keep the raid together, instead of trying to handle it myself.<br>
<br>
Machival Winterlong <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukitiari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kitiari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/10/02 6:34:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VS Tactics</span><hr size=1> VS is about fast damage and aggro control.  VS lifetap is a proc.  If you have low level melee there and VS riposte them the lifetap could go off ...thanks lowbie hp battery.  Key is to have a solid MA keeping aggro while all the other melees are at the rear to avoid riposte.  If you have the damage dealers VS will be dead before the chanters run oom from runing.  If not, ... Loading Please Wait.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udaktarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daktarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/10/02 6:58:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.citlink.net/citlink/s/siralleycat/Daktarr.jpg width=98 height=98></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VS Tactics</span><hr size=1> /agree Kitiari<br>
<br>
In addition to that, I feel it is important to have at least 3 wizards who can hit him with lure. You have to stand on his toes to cast on him.<br>
<br>
Now some tank types may say &quot;Oh we can do it with no wizards&quot; ... well /rude have fun dying buddy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src="http://www.citlink.net/~siralleycat/Dak-VI.jpg" border=3><br>
<b><i>Gnome Nuker of Vita Infinita</i></b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/14/02 5:35:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumwizard.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VS Tactics</span><hr size=1> Heh, sure if you got enough melee it can be done without wizards. Then again if you got enough wizards it can be done without melee <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Generally a mix works best, of course. For an average raid, 2 strong tanks, 5-6 melee damage dealers, 2 clerics, 2 chanters and a bunch of nukers (preferably wizards) works great. If you got it down right and have a very strong tank, you can do it with a single cleric and chanter as noone but the MA should get hurt. But that's a bit risky. The key, as kiti mentioned, is to make sure VS can't use your lower level tanks as HP batteries. Agro management is thus very important.<br>
<br>
Once you have the tank/chanter/cleric, the most important people for a VS raid are really the damage dealers. Especially wizards and rogues, with monks and rangers coming in after that. His lifetap really makes him a special mob, in that you can't compensate for low damage output by having more healing power. You either outdamage the lifetap proc by a significant amount, or you lose. If you don't do enough damage, it doesn't matter at all whether you have enough healers to keep the MA standing for 2 hours - you'll still lose.<br>
<br>
VS is a fairly low HP mob, though his lifetap makes him seem much more formidable. This is why fast damage dealers really shine. If you do damage fast enough, as wizards and rogues excel at, VS is a real pushover. If you have a raid that's losing, try adding another wizard or rogue and see how huge a difference it makes. 16.000hps is what VS has, if memory serves, and even a small group of the fast damage dealing classes can bring this down VERY fast. Often when you lose, it is because you are just barely outdamaging the lifetap, and therefore adding even a single wizard to the raid can turn the tables to make it look easy. <p>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
-Warder <BR>
